1
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:06,800
<i>I'll make you taste the same agony</i>

2
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,400
you caused my father.

3
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:11,800
<i>Ehi klai klai, piyan ma-ma.</i>

4
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,320
<i>Lasor!</i>

5
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,720
I'm warning you about your enemy.

6
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,880
Rip the Lek Lai out of his body.
Then you can kill him.

7
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:27,040
I'll drag you two down

8
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:29,160
to face the karma you created.

9
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:32,480
I'll find the evidence
to prove their innocence too.

10
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:36,360
I'll clear them of your accusations.

11
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:42,480
That black-masked bastard again?

12
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,800
I told you to look into him!

13
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,120
And you still haven't found anything?

14
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:53,200
Song said the man can't be shot or cut.

15
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:57,040
I think he must be someone with sorcery.

16
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:01,720
Could he be one of Lasor's men?

17
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,960
If he finds out we betrayed him,
we're completely finished.

18
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:13,640
His sister is in our hands, sir.
He won't dare do anything.

19
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:50,080
You bastards! Why did you capture me?

20
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:53,760
Watch your mouth.
You're standing before the governor.

21
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,200
It's fine. I don't mind.

22
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,800
After all, you're Lasor's little sister.

23
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,720
What does my brother have to do with this?

24
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,120
Lasor practices sorcery.

25
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,680
And worse, he's a bandit's son.

26
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,320
I never know when he might turn on me.

27
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:15,400
So I need you as leverage.

28
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,800
Or you could say as a hostage.

29
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,160
My brother
will never fall for your tricks.

30
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:30,000
Lasor is stupid. Stupid again and again.

31
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,640
Stupid like a buffalo.

32
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,920
Even if he dies and is reborn,

33
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,920
he still won't be smarter than us.

34
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:41,360
If Lasor finds out, he won't let you live.

35
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,640
I'm not afraid of your brother

36
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:49,320
because I have you.

37
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:09,680
Actually, you're young and pretty.

38
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,240
I think you'd be better off
cooperating with me.

39
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,680
Cooperating how?

40
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,320
If you become my woman

41
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:30,360
and persuade your brother
to swear loyalty to me,

42
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,640
I promise you both

43
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:36,560
power, fortune, and comfort for life.

44
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,520
Interested?

45
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,960
Let me think about it.

46
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:50,320
No need to think too long.
I can't hold back much longer.

47
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,920
You venomous snake!
You've got a lot of nerve!

48
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,360
One more step,

49
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:05,600
and you can start
planning your boss's funeral.

50
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,680
Yiwha?

51
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,160
Hey!

52
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:16,800
Back off! Back off!

53
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,800
Go.

54
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:37,320
The black-masked man. You die!

55
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,440
<i>Sangkhalikapi khanthakhanthang</i>
<i>tharangi niwirari.</i>

56
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:13,200
I surrender. Tell me what you want.

57
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:15,920
You're the one
who ordered Chin Seng's death, aren't you?

58
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,160
Yes.

59
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:24,360
I ordered Lasor and Pae to kill him.

60
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,560
You heard that clearly, didn't you?

61
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,920
And the slaughter
of Khun Yod Pakdee's family?

62
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,040
You were behind that too, weren't you?

63
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,880
Tell me the truth.

64
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,280
I don't know!

65
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:54,080
You're the one who sent men
to kill Khun Yod Pakdee

66
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,920
and framed my father and brother.

67
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,600
There's been an order from above.

68
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:16,720
I was ordered to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

69
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,320
By whom?

70
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,559
Phraya…

71
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,560
We have to get out of here. Now.

72
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:30,840
So now you finally see how rotten

73
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,160
your brother Lasor really is.

74
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,320
Lasor might've been used.

75
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,960
There's no proof he killed Chin Seng.

76
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:43,520
But he worked with Pae
and raided Chin Seng's house.

77
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,520
Do you still think
there's no blood on his hands

78
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:52,920
Before Duang died, he confessed
there was an order

79
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,640
to send people to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

80
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:59,360
But he died before he could finish.
The one who truly killed your father

81
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,160
must be that Phraya he mentioned.

82
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:05,520
He was afraid to die. He said
whatever would save his own skin.

83
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:09,320
If it wasn't true,
then why was he silenced?

84
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,800
Even if someone ordered Duang,

85
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:20,560
the ones
who brutally slaughtered my family

86
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,800
were still Lasor and Bandit Wad.

87
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,160
My father would never
do something that vile.

88
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:28,840
I'll drag them out
and make you see it with your own eyes.

89
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:34,000
You're blinded by hatred.

90
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,800
I'm done talking to you.

91
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:41,600
Someone's following us.

92
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,840
They're gone.

93
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,000
Where are you going?

94
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:06,520
To find proof that my father and brother
aren't the monsters you claim they are.

95
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:12,320
There must be something hidden
behind all this. The name just came out.

96
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:16,120
We can't go anywhere right now.
Duang was part of the government.

97
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:20,320
With him dead like this, the authorities
will hunt us down until they catch us.

98
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,040
I don't want to run away with you.

99
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:27,560
We're already in the same boat now.
If I let you go alone, you won't survive.

100
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:32,720
Besides, you can't die yet,

101
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,560
not until you see the consequences
of the karma your father created.

102
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,280
Yiam!

103
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,240
Let go. Let me go.

104
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:03,800
Duen… what should we do?

105
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:06,360
Dad has left us…

106
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:14,320
There were so many of you,
and you still let my father be killed.

107
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:22,320
When I regained consciousness,
everything was already like this.

108
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,440
His chest

109
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,440
was torn open, his heart ripped out.

110
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:32,600
Only a madman
could be that brutally savage.

111
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:36,160
Do you have any idea who did it?

112
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:39,800
If it wasn't Lasor's sister,
the daughter of Bandit Wad,

113
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,720
then it must have been
the masked man who helped her.

114
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,720
What does this have to do with Yiwha?

115
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:48,960
How would I know?
All I know is they're on the same side.

116
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,320
They killed the governor.

117
00:12:56,880 --> 00:13:01,000
Who exactly is that masked man?

118
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,400
Tim! Stop this right now! Tim!

119
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,000
I said stop!

120
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,640
What is this?

121
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,560
Phraya Dechanurak is dead.

122
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,720
You can't stay here anymore.

123
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:24,960
What right do you have to chase us out?

124
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:28,560
This is my father's residence.
Why can't I stay?

125
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:34,360
This is the governor's residence,
not your father's house.

126
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:38,680
A new governor is coming from the capital.

127
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:42,640
I must clean up all the trash
before he arrives.

128
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:48,040
But Duen and I have nowhere to go yet.
Can't you give us a little more time?

129
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:52,080
No. These are orders.

130
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:55,120
Take your things and leave.

131
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:09,440
A corpse-crow feather?

132
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:14,320
I was cleansing Lasor of the dark magic.

133
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:17,680
Someone sent corpse-crows to take him.

134
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,680
I fear it might be him.

135
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,680
There are many
who can summon corpse-crows.

136
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,720
It might not be him.

137
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:34,800
Besides, he already died.
We all saw it with our own eyes.

138
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:43,600
Petch!

139
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,400
And what if he isn't dead?

140
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,840
If he's still alive,
he would've shown himself by now.

141
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,720
Put your mind at ease, Wad.

142
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,640
Petch will never come back.

143
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:45,440
I'll go look for Lasor.

144
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,520
You two,
please help me take care of Yiwha.

145
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:58,520
Yiwha went to look for Lasor
at the governor's residence yesterday.

146
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,480
What did you say, Niem?

147
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,920
She went to question her brother

148
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:08,360
about Chin Seng's case, and Yod as well.

149
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,200
Yiwha…

150
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:14,360
Why does she always
bring trouble upon herself?

151
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,080
Search everywhere!

152
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:23,080
Someone's coming. Wad, hurry and run.

153
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:39,160
Search every corner. Go.

154
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,360
What's going on, Khun Paeng?

155
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:53,160
Prisoners escaped.
I'm here to look for them.

156
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:55,760
What crime did they commit
for you to come looking here?

157
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:59,800
They murdered Phraya Dechanurak,
the governor of Tha Khiri.

158
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:03,640
I suspect they're hiding here.

159
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:09,200
Since when did my house
become a hideout for violent criminals?

160
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:13,720
Since your niece
teamed up with that masked man

161
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,440
and killed the governor last night.

162
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,720
The masked man?

163
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,440
Yiwha killed the governor? Impossible.

164
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,760
Hey, Saeng!

165
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,720
Yes, sir.

166
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,440
Let's go.

167
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:39,840
Take them to the residence
for questioning.

168
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,320
Yes, sir.

169
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,200
Go. Walk.

170
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:49,000
- Go.
- I can walk on my own.

171
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,760
Walk.

172
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,880
- Hey.
- Walk.

173
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,200
I can walk on my own.

174
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,600
Hey? Dad--

175
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:26,720
Why did you stop me?
I'm going to help my dad.

176
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:31,040
Even if you go, you can't help.
Worse, you'd get arrested too.

177
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,680
So what do you want me to do?

178
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,640
Just stand by and watch them
take my dad away?

179
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:41,000
They hold all the power.

180
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:46,240
You have to think carefully.
Don't act rashly.

181
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:50,720
Otherwise, you'll end up dead
like a stray dog.

182
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:06,040
I need to send word to Pun right away.

183
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:41,000
Hey! You're blocking our way.

184
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,360
Are you looking to die?

185
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:50,400
Bandit Wad?

186
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:58,320
Release my friends and get lost.

187
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:03,960
Dream on. If you come any closer,
your friends will become forest ghosts.

188
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:09,400
Pathetic weapons like yours
can't do anything to them.

189
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,600
You wanna try?

190
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,080
Why don't we get serious then?

191
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,640
You're tough, huh?

192
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,520
I'll get back at you!

193
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:51,000
Hey! Why the rush?
I haven't even finished stretching yet.

194
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:55,000
Hey, don't forget,

195
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:59,280
disciples of Khao Phrom
never bully the weak.

196
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,400
Chaem, Niem,

197
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,880
I have something
I need you two to help me with.

198
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:10,400
PATROL UNIT

199
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,960
Khun Paeng testified

200
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:18,800
that Bandit Wad intercepted
Uncle Niem and Uncle Chaem

201
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:21,080
while they were being escorted
for interrogation at the residence.

202
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,720
Where is my dad now? Is he safe?

203
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,480
I don't know.

204
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:31,840
But judging by Khun Paeng's condition,
I think your dad should be fine.

205
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:42,280
I think Uncle Chaem,
Uncle Niem, and Bandit Wad

206
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,440
are trying to find a way
to help Yiwha right now.

207
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,800
I never thought Yiwha
would dare kill the governor.

208
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:53,880
I don't believe it either,
but Khun Paeng insists

209
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:58,120
that Yiwha and the masked man
murdered Phraya Decha.

210
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,920
The masked man? Again?

211
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,720
This is starting to feel
far from ordinary.

212
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,600
What does the masked man
have to do with this?

213
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:14,240
Does he even know Yiwha?

214
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,520
The masked man
handed Song and Pae over to the police.

215
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,200
He was also present at Duang's death.

216
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:31,720
That means he's here
specifically to punish the wicked.

217
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,440
Right now, the police
are trying to gather clues.

218
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,080
That mysterious masked man

219
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:44,640
might also know something
about Lasor's disappearance.

220
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:53,680
The one who probably knows the most
is Tim,

221
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:59,400
but he'll never confess,
no matter what happens.

222
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:09,920
Don't forget. There's still Bandit Pae.

223
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,000
GUARDING SCHEDULE
DAENG, MHAN

224
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:22,760
Pae,

225
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:26,800
are you ready to confess yet?

226
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:30,640
No. I'm not ready.

227
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:33,880
Phraya Decha,
the governor, has been murdered.

228
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,680
If you keep your mouth shut,

229
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,520
more people will die because of you.

230
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:49,920
The governor is dead?

231
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:55,840
Yes. And the next one could be you.

232
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,280
Can you stop pressuring me?

233
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,120
I'm already stressed to death as it is.

234
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,960
If you don't tell the truth,

235
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,520
there's nothing I can do to help you.

236
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:40,120
Just wait until it's my turn.

237
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,480
Where are we going, Duen?

238
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:45,680
Stupid question.
We'll find a way back to the capital.

239
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:48,240
It's far. How are we getting there?
Do you even know the way?

240
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:53,120
Where are you two beauties headed?

241
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:56,080
None of your business.

242
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:57,520
Move aside.

243
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,440
Well, well. Feisty? I like that.

244
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,040
Hey.

245
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,520
You take the older one.

246
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:06,160
I'll take the younger.

247
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:09,800
Hey! Follow them!

248
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:10,720
Where are you going?

249
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:25,040
Please let us go.
Don't hurt me and my sister.

250
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:27,120
Let you go? Sure.

251
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,360
After you become our women.

252
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:34,920
I'd rather die
than be the woman of hell-beasts like you.

253
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:36,840
Big mouth, huh?

254
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:57,560
Lasor.

255
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:24,280
<i>Pathamang phinthukang</i>
<i>chatang, trinikattawa, nana.</i>

256
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:29,280
Hurry up.

257
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:31,640
The tracks go this way.

258
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:40,200
Where did the tracks go?

259
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:41,560
Where did he go?

260
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,920
Did he fly?

261
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:49,040
Yeah. That masked man
must have powerful sorcery.

262
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,160
Idiot!

263
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:54,360
No human can fly.

264
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:57,600
No matter how strong his magic is,
he won't escape me.

265
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:00,920
I'll drag him out and rip his heart out.

266
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:03,840
Go. Search everywhere.

267
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:10,240
WANTED DEAD
MASKED MAN, YIWHA

268
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:15,800
Idiot! You couldn't catch the masked man
and you still dare show your face?

269
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,080
Whoa!

270
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:21,560
Sir, we searched

271
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,720
the entire forest, but found no trace.

272
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:28,680
Could they have fled Tha Khiri?

273
00:27:29,320 --> 00:27:33,520
He ran with Yiwha.
They can't have gone far.

274
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:39,280
But Yiwha's as capable as any grown man.

275
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,920
She's still a woman.

276
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:47,120
Hurry up. Gather more men.

277
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:51,160
We must catch the masked man and Yiwha
before the new governor arrives.

278
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:53,960
- Go!
- Yes, sir.

279
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:21,200
Tim's men are gone.
But they'll come back for sure.

280
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,040
Then we should split up.

281
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:27,120
I don't like following orders.

282
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:30,240
To wait, to eat, to sleep.

283
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:32,400
Here.

284
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,480
Take it.

285
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:38,800
We split up here.

286
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:43,080
You never listen.

287
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:45,760
Look at this.

288
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:52,000
WANTED DEAD
MASKED MAN, YIWHA

289
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,600
By now, your face must be everywhere.

290
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,040
How are you supposed to escape alone?

291
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:01,080
I can survive on my own.

292
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:03,000
And where exactly are you planning to go?

293
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,680
If you can't think of anything,
come with me.

294
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:11,200
We'll hide for now
until we find who really killed Duang.

295
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,760
That's final. Follow me.

296
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:18,440
Ordering again.

297
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:23,760
You must be tired. Let's rest.

298
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,240
I'm not tired.

299
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:32,760
- You're hungry, right?
- I'm not.

300
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:41,040
Do I have to feed you myself?

301
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,480
So where are we going to hide?

302
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:07,000
Khao Phrom.

303
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:12,480
Old Master Khrua Phut
will get dragged into trouble.

304
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,840
We won't hide there for long.

305
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:20,040
Old Master Khrua Phut is well-versed
in both white and black sorcery.

306
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,560
He'll definitely know

307
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:25,760
whose handiwork those black claws were,
the ones that ripped Duang's heart out.

308
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,040
Why are you following us?

309
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,680
I'm just following.

310
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,960
- Just get lost. Go!
- Duen.

311
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:56,400
It's good to have Lasor with us.

312
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:59,040
What if the forest bandits come back?

313
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:03,480
Someone like him is no different
from low-class forest bandits.

314
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:08,560
Lasor, I'm sorry.

315
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:12,440
Duen is still shaken.
She spoke without thinking.

316
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:17,440
I don't mind.

317
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:23,040
Dogs bark. They don't bite.

318
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:27,960
You hell spawn! Are you calling me a dog?

319
00:31:28,040 --> 00:31:31,560
You dog-born bastard!

320
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:35,200
- Duen, enough.
- How dare you?

321
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:38,960
We're lucky Lasor came to protect us.

322
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:43,240
Or do you want to risk our lives
and let bandits kill and rape us for real?

323
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:06,880
I'm so exhausted.

324
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:10,400
Hang in there, Duen.

325
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,720
Where did Lasor go?

326
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:26,160
He abandoned us for sure.

327
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,840
I knew it. That rotten bandit.

328
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:33,360
Once he saw we had no valuables,
he disappeared.

329
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:34,520
See, Duangjai?

330
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:37,880
Did you say he'd protect us?
How did you believe that?

331
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:40,640
Damn lunatic bandit!

332
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:49,560
Lasor went to fetch our bags. See?

333
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:51,400
Lasor.

334
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:56,840
Where did you disappear to?

335
00:33:14,840 --> 00:33:16,760
Our gold and jewels are all still here.

336
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:20,560
Thank you so much, Lasor.

337
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:24,480
The bags were far away.
You came back in no time.

338
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:26,080
You're really amazing.

339
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:31,120
Let's go bathe and change clothes.

340
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,440
I'm sticky all over.

341
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,440
Don't follow us.

342
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:59,760
- Duangjai.
- Yes, Duen?

343
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:03,320
Do you think he's sneaking around?

344
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:06,800
I'm right here.
What's there to be afraid of?

345
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:11,440
You never know.
You can't trust bandit scum like him.

346
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:16,600
Whoa, Duen. Lasor wouldn't sneak around
watching you bathe.

347
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,600
I'll say this now.

348
00:34:18,679 --> 00:34:21,120
I'll only let him escort us to the pier.

349
00:34:21,199 --> 00:34:23,520
After that, I'll kick him far away.

350
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:46,960
What are you waiting for?
This is the perfect chance.

351
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:48,960
Make her yours.

352
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:51,480
I have something important to do.

353
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:55,520
I must destroy
the Lek Lai inside Yiam first.

354
00:34:56,880 --> 00:35:00,680
And I must eliminate everyone who knows

355
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:04,440
that I caused Khun Yod's family
to be slaughtered.

356
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:07,840
You can't deal with that yet.

357
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:11,200
The police are hunting you.
Handle what's in front of you first.

358
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:15,720
This is a golden opportunity.
You'll get what you want.

359
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:23,120
But Lady Duen

360
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:27,120
hates me to the bone.

361
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:30,000
Then just force her. She'll be tamed.

362
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:34,000
Nui. Mind your own damn business.

363
00:35:34,680 --> 00:35:37,280
Don't worry. I'll take care of it myself.

364
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,240
Nui, don't.

365
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:52,800
Come sit here, closer to the fire.

366
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,200
You'll freeze to death.

367
00:36:06,560 --> 00:36:10,040
I won't die that easily.
I'm a bandit's daughter.

368
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:12,840
But you're the son of a noble lord.

369
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,480
Now you're circling back
to your father again?

370
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:20,160
Your father, Bandit Wad,
slaughtered my entire family.

371
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:21,920
I saw it with my own eyes.

372
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,840
Do you know that Yiam,

373
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:31,240
Khun Yod's son, is still alive.

374
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:33,480
He escaped that night.

375
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,000
How do you know?

376
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,480
I met him.

377
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,560
Then where is he now?

378
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:45,280
What's wrong?
You went quiet all of a sudden.

379
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:52,040
Nothing. It's nothing.
But my father would never kill a friend.

380
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:56,720
Your father is a bandit. That's why he
did something so despicable to a friend.

381
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,000
It's time.

382
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:31,720
Time for what?

383
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:35,040
Time to ascend to heaven.

384
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,440
I'll take care of her little sister.

385
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,360
Stop right there, Nui.

386
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:43,080
I can't stop.

387
00:37:44,480 --> 00:37:48,120
I've wanted to try it for so long,
wanted to taste it for so long.

388
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,760
What are you going to do?

389
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:55,600
What are you--

390
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:57,000
Lasor? How dare you lay a hand on me?

391
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:58,360
You bastard!

392
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,120
Lady Duen.

393
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,280
Duangjai?

394
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:13,000
Duangjai! Duangjai!

395
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,920
What did you do to my sister?

396
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:21,800
What did you do? Where is my sister?

397
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:25,560
Where is my sister?

398
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,720
<i>Ohm, sacred gaze,</i>

399
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:29,080
<i>bind her sight, ensnare her eyes.</i>

400
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,760
What are you doing?

401
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:59,960
Oh, I'm cold.

402
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:04,680
Thought you said
bandits' daughters don't get cold.

403
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:01,800
Nui! Stop!

404
00:42:05,080 --> 00:42:06,160
No!

405
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:11,960
Nui!

406
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:15,680
You don't see me
as your master anymore, do you?

407
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:20,960
Lasor, I did it for you.

408
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:24,840
For me? You did it for yourself!

409
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:27,080
You wanted human flesh
and you used my name!

410
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:30,640
No. No, Lasor. No…

411
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:03,520
Duangjai…

412
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:16,800
Duangjai…

413
00:44:19,440 --> 00:44:22,880
Lasor! How could you let my sister die?!

414
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,200
You bastard! Why wasn't it you instead?!

415
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:27,160
Huh?! Why wasn't it you instead?!

416
00:44:30,040 --> 00:44:32,920
Lady Duen.

417
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:35,800
I'm sorry.

418
00:44:42,120 --> 00:44:43,800
Sorry?!

419
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:47,160
Sorry?

420
00:44:47,240 --> 00:44:50,360
Sorry?

421
00:44:52,560 --> 00:44:53,480
Sorry?

422
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:57,440
Will my sister come back to life then?

423
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,280
You're gone.

424
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:05,880
How can I live alone?

425
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:09,400
Why did you leave me?

426
00:45:09,480 --> 00:45:12,200
Why did you leave me?

427
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:25,120
Don't, my lady.

428
00:45:29,360 --> 00:45:31,520
She was mauled by a tiger.

429
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:33,000
It's not a sight you should see.

430
00:45:33,760 --> 00:45:36,120
Then how did my sister get mauled

431
00:45:37,240 --> 00:45:39,800
without me knowing?

432
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:47,000
I was half-asleep.

433
00:45:50,040 --> 00:45:52,400
I remember…

434
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:04,240
you… I saw you…

435
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:10,680
It wasn't me. It was a spirit tiger,

436
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:14,080
a tiger possessed by an evil soul.

437
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:36,080
Don't worry, my lady.

438
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:39,480
I will protect you

439
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:41,880
with my life.

440
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:11,960
My plan worked. See?

441
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:13,600
Nui!

442
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:23,680
Lasor, I just want you to be happy.

443
00:48:30,920 --> 00:48:32,840
Don't ever act without my order again.

444
00:48:34,920 --> 00:48:38,680
Don't kill anyone unnecessarily.
Otherwise,

445
00:48:40,040 --> 00:48:41,840
I'll send you back into the grave.

446
00:48:41,920 --> 00:48:45,920
Lasor, I'm scared now.

447
00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:51,680
But what about you and the lady?

448
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:04,800
If I used sorcery,

449
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:09,840
I'd only get your body,
only for a fleeting moment.

450
00:49:12,520 --> 00:49:14,160
I'll make you

451
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,320
love this man, Lasor.

452
00:49:18,480 --> 00:49:22,520
I want all both your body and your heart.

453
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:51,520
Not your business.

454
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:37,480
<i>Wiwi buddho iti…</i>

455
00:51:02,360 --> 00:51:04,760
Why am I back here again?

456
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,240
Yiam.

457
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:18,000
I should thank your sleeping smoke.
It gave me a nice rest.

458
00:51:18,960 --> 00:51:22,000
So, how was walking
in the forest all night? Fun?

459
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,520
This was your doing.

460
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:34,160
Let me go.

461
00:51:34,240 --> 00:51:35,120
Let go.

462
00:51:35,840 --> 00:51:38,040
Let me go my own way.

463
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:41,640
I can't stay with someone who wants
to kill my father and my brother.

464
00:51:43,560 --> 00:51:45,960
Once you're safe, I'll leave you.

465
00:51:47,560 --> 00:51:49,800
There's no safe place for me anymore.

466
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:54,000
But you still have a way out.
They don't know who the masked man is yet.

467
00:51:55,040 --> 00:51:56,800
Why are you running away with me?

468
00:51:58,560 --> 00:52:02,120
You slipped away
because you were worried about me.

469
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:10,400
I wasn't worried.

470
00:52:11,720 --> 00:52:13,280
I just didn't want to be your burden.

471
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:17,440
That's what worry is.

472
00:52:35,240 --> 00:52:36,480
Yiwha…

473
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:42,120
I swore I wouldn't soften my heart.

474
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:48,040
I won't soften mine either.

475
00:52:58,680 --> 00:52:59,960
Dad.

476
00:53:13,360 --> 00:53:15,240
What?

477
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:20,400
Whoa. Wad walks like he's flying.

478
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:23,240
Maybe he's using
a shortening-distance spell.

479
00:53:24,120 --> 00:53:27,560
Yeah. He's regained a lot of his strength.

480
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:30,920
But he was rushing
because he said he found some clues.

481
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:31,960
What clues?

482
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:33,920
Then follow him. So we'll find out.

483
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:36,440
Who are they?

484
00:53:42,560 --> 00:53:45,040
I don't know. I don't know them.

485
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:57,080
How did you get here?

486
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:05,920
So the masked man was you.

487
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:10,520
<i>Buddho me natho, Dhammo me natho,</i>

488
00:54:10,600 --> 00:54:11,680
<i>Sangho me natho…</i>

489
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:14,040
<i>Saka pha cha Bucha cha maha bucha Issawa</i>

490
00:54:14,120 --> 00:54:17,320
<i>su Itipiso bhagava.</i>
<i>Lek Lai, awaken and grow.</i>

491
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:23,440
Yiam, don't. Listen to me first.

492
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:30,160
Yiam!

493
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:32,800
Don't!

494
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:44,880
The power of Lek Lai…

495
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:08,120
<i>Master, I'm not driven by hatred.</i>
<i>I'm punishing evil.</i>

496
00:55:09,120 --> 00:55:10,560
<i>Mettancha</i>

497
00:55:11,120 --> 00:55:14,480
<i>sabba lokasming mana sambhavaye…</i>

498
00:55:14,560 --> 00:55:17,200
<i>Buddho lalui, dha lalui, ya.</i>
<i>Release your mind.</i>

499
00:55:23,840 --> 00:55:25,600
Wad?

500
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:28,200
Wad!

501
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:30,120
- Uncle Niem.
- Wad.

502
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:32,080
- Hey, how are you?
- Wad.

503
00:55:37,240 --> 00:55:39,200
- Yiam!
- Wad.

504
00:55:39,280 --> 00:55:41,000
Go after Yiam.

505
00:55:41,080 --> 00:55:42,600
Stop, Yiam.

506
00:55:53,520 --> 00:55:55,000
Extinguish the three fires…

507
00:55:56,280 --> 00:56:00,520
Let go. Accept. Be calm.

508
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:05,000
Yiam, calm your mind.

509
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:08,560
Now that you've seen my father,
let's talk first.

510
00:56:09,160 --> 00:56:10,320
I won't talk!

511
00:56:10,840 --> 00:56:11,800
Yiam.

512
00:56:13,280 --> 00:56:14,400
Stop right now.

513
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:17,760
You are a righteous man,
that is why you can wield the Lek Lai.

514
00:56:18,800 --> 00:56:21,080
But never use a sacred power for evil.

515
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:22,480
Or it will turn against you.

516
00:56:24,640 --> 00:56:28,520
Listen.
We were your father's sworn brothers.

517
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:36,200
<i>Na!</i>

518
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:45,960
Yiam, don't!

519
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:50,480
Lek Lai exists to punish evil,
not to avenge.

520
00:56:51,920 --> 00:56:53,440
Or its power will turn on you.

521
00:56:53,520 --> 00:56:57,440
I'd rather die!
I'll die right here with you!

522
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:05,040
<i>Your time's up, Pae.</i>

523
00:57:05,120 --> 00:57:07,280
<i>Confess everything.</i>

524
00:57:07,360 --> 00:57:08,880
You want to die that badly?

525
00:57:08,960 --> 00:57:12,000
Don't do anything foolish.
Do you want to die?

526
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:13,400
You're the one who must die.

527
00:57:13,480 --> 00:57:16,720
Today I'll kill you,
so my dad can finally rest in peace.

528
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:21,760
Look up.

529
00:57:21,840 --> 00:57:24,160
If you want to kill my master,
step over my dead body first.

530
00:57:24,240 --> 00:57:26,120
If you think this bastard is so righteous,

531
00:57:26,200 --> 00:57:27,400
don't call yourself my son.

532
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:31,240
He intends to use Lasor
as a pawn to take revenge on me,

533
00:57:31,320 --> 00:57:33,520
<i>but I have something</i>
<i>I need your help with.</i>

534
00:58:17,880 --> 00:58:19,880
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
